Method Detail

equals

boolean equals(java.lang.Object otherCollection)
Checks whether a collection is the same object as another. There is not currently any specific implementation overriding standard Java functionality. This will not return true if two different NoteCollections containt the same notes, just if they are the same Java object.

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object
Parameters:
otherCollection - Object other collection to compare with
Returns:
true boolean if successful
Since:
org.openntf.domino 2.5.0

setSelectOptions

void setSelectOptions(java.util.Set<NoteCollection.SelectOption> options)
Loads a set of SelectOption enums to be used for creating the collection. This is the preferred method over using the specific setters, to ensure easy access to all valid options.

Parameters:
options - Set enum values corresponding to desired note types
Since:
org.openntf.domino 2.5.0
